// Workspace file: lets local development work on the core module
// (./) and the Caddy adapter submodule (./caddymodule) together as
// one unit, without committing a `replace` directive into either
// go.mod. With this file present, `go build`, `go test` and `xcaddy
// --with pkg=$REPO_ROOT/caddymodule` all see in-tree edits to the
// core module immediately — no tag bump or `go mod download`
// roundtrip needed.
//
// Downstream consumers (anyone running `xcaddy --with
// github.com/VeloxCoding/scopecache/caddymodule@vX.Y.Z`) do NOT use
// this file: workspaces are a main-module-only concept, identical
// to how `replace` directives are ignored when a module is pulled
// in as a dependency. They get the require'd version of the core
// module from the module proxy, exactly as if this file did not
// exist.
//
// Set GOWORK=off to disable the workspace for one command — useful
// when running `go mod tidy` in caddymodule to make sure go.sum
// reflects the published version, not the local override.

go 1.25.0

use (
	.
	./caddymodule
)
